empirical industrial organization a progress report siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display empirical industrial organization a progress report type siepr discussion paper 09 010 author s liran einav jonathan levin published 02 23 10 download pdf abstract the field of industrial organization has made dramatic advances over the last few decades in developing empirical methods for analyzing imperfect competition and the organization of markets we describe the motivation for these developments and some of the successes we also discuss the relative emphasis that applied work in the field has placed on economic theory relative to statistical research design and the possibility that a focus on methodological innovation has crowded out applications we offer some suggestions about how the field may progress in coming years stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
